column4: Can someone help me?, I just installed a program and I am having alot of problems finding it.
what program?
frostwire
where did you get it from?
www.frostwire.com
was it a deb file?
did you look in all your menus?
yes
try doing 'frostfire" from teh command line
please explain how to get to command line?
if you want it in your menu you can look in /usr/share/applications and see if there's a .desktop file for it, and let me know if there is
explain how to do that?, (im one day into linux)
APplications->Accessories->Terminal
ok.
im in the terminal.
or put it in the box that you get when you do alt-f2
i typed frostwire in the terminal and it did not load.
do 'dpkg -L frostfire' in terminal
look for something in a bin folder like /bin  /usr/bin, and then try to run that
I have to get a newer java...
and it says my file type .bin is not supported...
